  "text": "The xDS configuration delivery chain has three layers: (1) Proto definitions in data-plane-api define the wire protocol \u2014 DiscoveryRequest/DiscoveryResponse messages in discovery.proto and the AggregatedDiscoveryService with StreamAggregatedResources/DeltaAggregatedResources RPCs in ads.proto. (2) go-control-plane implements the server side \u2014 discovery.pb.go has the generated Go types for DiscoveryRequest/DiscoveryResponse, ads_grpc.pb.go has the generated gRPC service interface, pkg/server/v3/server.go implements StreamAggregatedResources which delegates to pkg/server/sotw/v3/server.go's StreamHandler to process the bidirectional stream. (3) Envoy's C++ data plane implements the client side \u2014 SubscriptionFactoryImpl (source/common/config/) creates subscriptions, GrpcSubscriptionImpl (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/) adapts typed subscriptions to the GrpcMux interface, and GrpcMuxImpl plus the xds_mux/ variants manage the actual gRPC streams that send DiscoveryRequests and process DiscoveryResponses.",
